cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a neural network-based recommendation model that focuses on modeling non-linear user-item interactions for personalized recommendations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to recommendation systems. Additionally, since the paper deals with real-world datasets, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text-based recommendations, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category.
